---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Social Proof for Event Photographers — Collect & Display Client Testimonials | SocialProof.dev">
  <main class="for-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="badge">For Event Photographers</div>
        <h1>Turn emotional delivery-day reactions into bookings</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">When you hand over a gallery and the client cries happy tears — that's your best marketing moment. SocialProof captures it instantly, before the feeling fades.</p>
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/register" class="btn-primary">Start free — no credit card</a>
        <p class="micro">Free forever for 1 active widget</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="problem">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>You're great at capturing moments. Why is capturing reviews so hard?</h2>
        <p>Event photography lives and dies by reputation. A potential client considers your portfolio, then immediately looks for social proof — what did real clients think? How did you handle the chaos? Were the photos delivered on time?</p>
        <p>Those answers exist. Your past clients would give you glowing reviews. But by the time you remember to ask, weeks have passed and the momentum is gone.</p>
        <p>SocialProof lets you ask at the perfect moment — when you deliver the gallery — and makes it so easy that most clients actually respond.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="benefits">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>The testimonial tool photographers actually use</h2>
        <div class="benefits-grid">
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>⚡ Ask at delivery, get replies instantly</h3>
            <p>Include your collection link in your gallery delivery email. Clients are emotional and appreciative — conversion is highest in this window.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>🖼️ Optional photo uploads</h3>
            <p>Clients can attach a photo from their event — their face next to a beautiful print, a snapshot of their album. Social proof with visuals converts.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>⭐ Star ratings alongside text</h3>
            <p>Build a 5-star reputation on your own site, not just on Google or Yelp where you don't control the presentation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>🎨 Matches your brand</h3>
            <p>The widget adapts to your site's styling. Minimalist, editorial, or bold — it blends in rather than screaming "third-party widget."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>✅ Full approval control</h3>
            <p>Every testimonial goes through your dashboard before it's public. Choose exactly what story you tell.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>📍 Works everywhere</h3>
            <p>Squarespace, Pixieset, Format, Showit, WordPress — any site that accepts custom code gets your testimonials widget.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sample-widget">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Here's what it looks like on your portfolio</h2>
        <div class="widget-preview">
          <blockquote>
            <p>"Marcus anticipated every moment I didn't even know I wanted captured. Our gallery was delivered in 4 days and I've looked at it every single day since. Worth every penny — and I don't say that lightly about photography."</p>
            <footer>— Priya S., Chicago IL · ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</footer>
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <p>Real client words. On your portfolio. Converting new inquiries on autopilot.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="how-it-works">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Up and running in under 15 minutes</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li><strong>Sign up free</strong> at app.socialproof.dev</li>
          <li><strong>Copy your collection link</strong> — works for every client, one URL</li>
          <li><strong>Add it to your gallery delivery email template</strong> — one time setup</li>
          <li><strong>Approve incoming testimonials</strong> from your dashboard</li>
          <li><strong>Add one script tag</strong> to your portfolio or contact page</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Photographer FAQs</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do clients need to log in or create an account?</h3>
            <p>Never. They open a link, type their thoughts, hit submit. It takes 60 seconds and there's no barrier.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can I ask clients to attach a photo from their event?</h3>
            <p>Yes — there's an optional image upload in the form. Clients can add a headshot, a favorite photo from their event, or their album cover.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>I already have Google reviews. Do I need this too?</h3>
            <p>Google reviews are great for local search. SocialProof lets you display curated testimonials on your own portfolio in the exact visual style you choose — you control the layout, placement, and which reviews get featured.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How do I add it to my Squarespace portfolio?</h3>
            <p>Squarespace accepts custom code blocks. Add your widget script tag in a Code Block wherever you want testimonials to appear. Takes about 2 minutes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Ready to turn your happiest clients into your best salespeople?</h2>
        <p>Start collecting testimonials today. The moment you deliver a gallery is the perfect moment to ask.</p>
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/register" class="btn-primary">Start free today</a>
        <p class="micro">Free forever for 1 active widget · No credit card required</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
